Definition.WordDefinition:
Feline \Fe"line\, a. [L. felinus, fr. feles, felis, cat, prob. orig., the fruitful: cf. F. f['e]lin. See {Fetus}.] 1. (Zo["o]l.) Catlike; of or pertaining to the genus {Felis}, or family {Felid[ae]}; as, the feline race; feline voracity. [1913 Webster]
2. Characteristic of cats; sly; stealthy; treacherous; as, a feline nature; feline manners. [1913 Webster]
feline adj : of or relating to cats; "feline fur" n : any of various lithe-bodied round-headed fissiped mammals many with retractile claws [syn: {felid}]
